                <head>189. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 26, Secretary-General Hammarskjöld addressed the <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">U.N</gloss>. General Assembly, responding to criticism of
                    the United Nations and its Secretariat which Chairman <persName
                        corresp="#p_KNS2">Khrushchev</persName> had voiced 3 days earlier. <hi
                        rend="italic">The New York Times</hi> reported that as <persName
                        corresp="#p_HD3">Hammarskjöld</persName> spoke, <persName corresp="#p_KNS2"
                        >Khrushchev</persName> pounded his fist on his desk. Other members of the
                    Soviet Delegation joined him. (September 27, 1960, page A16) For a record of
                    these proceedings and the text of <persName corresp="#p_HD3"
                        >Hammarskjöld</persName>’s statement, see U.N. doc. <gloss target="#t_A1"
                        >A</gloss>/PV.871.</p>
            </div>
